not a bad beer... tasty and refreshing...a little bitter at colder temps...easy to drink warm...nuts, brown, minimal head, light sweetness, medium bitterness, medium sourness, soft carbonation, bitter,
i love the brown wonder of a beer...it is nutty & yummy...i really enjoy this beer & like to have one often...nuts, roasty, brown, minimal head, medium sweetness, lightly bitter,
this beer just tastes good...from start to finish, this is my go to beer when i cannot make a choice...it is easy to drink but not a guzzler...i can even drink it warm.

i am not sure how to explain ruby...she tastes good but sometimes she tastes flat...i have recently started having Rubinators (Ruby & Terminator Stout blend) because it gives Ruby just what she needs to be perfect...I have to say that i never go anywhere near a McMenamins without stopping in & grabbing a Ruby
1st swig = yum....by the 3rd I am chugging this stuff.... unfortunately, it is cost prohibitive to drink ...if you do not like beer - like me - this is a good one

First swig is a little shocking....i do love a fruity beer but whoa man....the overly fruity nature of this beer did grow on me & by the time i finished it - i already had another waiting to go down...for a non-beer drinker, this one is pretty nice.

the one thing i hate about this beer is the fact that i cannot breath thru my nose without the nasty smells after swallowing....this beer gets the prohibition treatment - poured to the drain before .25 of the bottle is gone.

by the 3rd i am drinking it fast ...
